Class ImplementorForAbstractClasses

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
ClassCreator
Direct Known Subclasses:
FunctionalMockImplementorForAbstractClasses, Impl4Abstract
public class ImplementorForAbstractClasses
extends AbstractClassCreator

ClassCreator that creates a concrete subclass of an abstract class.
This composer can create a concrete class that extends a specified abstract class. This class composer supports the following annotations:

  • Property
  • DelegateProperties
  • Delegate2Map
  • DelegateMethods
    • The new class will not have any new field, it will only have the methods necessary to implement the interfaces declared by the abstract class.
